          <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">
              <tr> 
                <td colspan="2" align="center" bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><img src="../img/describe.gif" alt="Description" name="Describe" width="350" height="45" border="0" id="Describe"></td>
              </tr>
        <tr align="left" valign="top"> 
          <td colspan="3"><p><img border="0" src="images/shirakabeso_images/shirakabeso_outside1.jpg" alt="Shirakabeso" width="250" height="186"></p>
            <p><b>Location:</b> Central Izu Peninsula, Shizuoka Prefecture</p>
            <p>Located in the center of the Izu Peninsula, Shirakabeso is a <b>Traditional Ryokan</b> (see definition of ryokan styles below) and it has a special architectural design with broad tiled roofs, white plaster walls, and black pillars and beams. Each of the 29 guest rooms at Shirakabeso has a different shape and style, and each is named after an Izu folk tale. Shirakabeso boasts 2 very special baths. One bath is carved from a 53 ton rock, and another is carved out of a 1,200 year old rosewood tree trunk. There are other outdoor and indoor baths as well at Shirakabeso. All baths are open 24 hours a day. Seafood and wild boar hot-pot are served for dinner, and guests can enjoy fresh "wasabi" (Japanese horseradish) picked from the nearby streams. Check-in time is after 14:30 and check-out time is before 10:30am. Parking is available. <b>If you request a reservation at Shirakabeso, please use a VISA or MasterCard - this ryokan does not deal with American Express. Thank you.</b></p><p><a href="JavaScript:traditional()"><img src="../img/type.gif" alt="Type" name="Type" width="54" height="18" border="0" align="absmiddle" id="Type"></a><a href="JavaScript:traditional()">Traditional Ryokan</a>
